<h1 class="mb-4">Create Course</h1>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-8">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
        <h5 class="mb-0">Course Details</h5>
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <form action="/courses" method="POST">
          <div class="mb-3">
            <label for="name" class="form-label">Course Name</label>
            <input
              type="text"
              id="name"
              name="name"
              class="form-control"
              placeholder="Enter course name"
              required
            />
          </div>
          <div class="mb-3">
            <label for="description" class="form-label">Description</label>
            <textarea
              id="description"
              name="description"
              class="form-control"
              rows="5"
              placeholder="Enter course description"
              required
            ></textarea>
          </div>
          <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Create Course</button>
          <a href="/courses" class="btn btn-secondary">Cancel</a>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header bg-info text-white">
        <h5 class="mb-0">Tips</h5>
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <p>A good course should have:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Clear, descriptive name</li>
          <li>Detailed description of what will be covered</li>
          <li>Structured content with examinations</li>
        </ul>
        <p>After creating a course, you can:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Add examinations</li>
          <li>Assign it to members</li>
          <li>View results</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>